The paper proposes a framework for analyzing skin lesion images using a convolutional neural network (CNN) and class activation maps (CAMs). This involves image classification and region cropping, which are common tasks in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of CAMs also suggests a focus on interpretability and explainability, which are important topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper deals with medical imaging, which is a subfield of multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
